Ask HN: Are you open to sharing your thoughts on the CI/CD Tooling Market?
text:
Note: This post was run by the mod team before posting and they're happy for it to be here.

I'm a Snr-PM at Atlassian who's recently taken over leading Bitbucket Cloud's CI/CD product (Bitbucket Pipelines).

I'm really keen to get a deeper understanding of the key challenges faced by teams that regularly use CI/CD tools today and felt the Hacker News community might be a place where some people with some opinions might be found.

Why should you get involved? Well I'm doing this off my own back so unfortunately I don't have $100 Amazon Gift Cards to throw around.

But I do believe that this community understands that a more competitive DevOps tooling market is a good thing for everyone. It drives innovation and better outcomes for customers of all DevOps products - not just Bitbucket.

So, if you're open to a conversation, come fill out my lovely Google Form and I will be in touch: https://forms.gle/D4ZUQec3S9n4pkbZ9

--- Something resembling verification: https://www.linkedin.com/posts/edmund-munday_devops-tooling-scm-cicd-research-activity-6995913239515607040-FBXa?utm_source=share&utm_medium=member_desktop
